title: Did the 2020 election run away from the end?
subtitle: Even as Joe Biden obtained the majority of the electoral votes in the United States presidential election in 2020, President Donald Trump refused to surrender.
author: Jessica Lee
vclaim: Until mid-November 2020, the United States presidential election remained "out of sight," and there was therefore uncertainty about the outcome that United States President Donald Trump could logically claim to remain the winner.
